OL,4,CChernobyl radiation damage 'not passed
OL,5,Cto children'
OL,6, There is no "additional DNA damage" in
OL,7, children born to parents who were
OL,8, exposed to radiation from the Chernobyl
OL,9, explosion before they were conceived.
OL,11,FThis is according to the first study to
OL,12,Fscreen the genes of children whose
OL,13,Fparents were enlisted to help in the
OL,14,Fclean-up after the nuclear accident.
OL,16,FParticipants, all conceived after the
OL,17,Fdisaster and born between 1987 and
OL,18,F2002, had their whole genomes screened.
OL,20,FThe study found no mutations that were
OL,21,Fassociated with a parent's exposure.
